description: Memories of the drummer Cozy Cole -- his precise time and long solos, his time with Henry "Red" Allen and Cab Calloway -- as well as memories of discrimination on the road, the house rat, with a story about Benny Carter, heroic eater.  Recorded by Michael Steinman for JAZZ LIVES (http://www.jazzlives.wordpress.com).
